Principles of quality management in a health care institution and the quality of management activities; the manager's tasks aimed to assure the quality of a service. Process management and description of processes. Health service standards 1, 4 and 5 of health promoting hospitals: management policy, promotion of a healthy workplace, and implementation and monitoring of activities related to clinical health promotion. Possibilities of applying the principles of quality management in nursing practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To deepen the knowledge of the principles of quality management and explain the possibilities to apply them for the provision of a health service.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course: - knows the fundamentals of quality management and the mechanisms of quality assurance in health care; - is able to describe the processes related to the provision of health services;  - orientate themselves in the legal acts that regulate health care quality; - is able to apply the principles of quality management for the planning of a health service.
